01/10/2006
PALIC, Serbia -- An OSCE-run training course for police chiefs from eight Southeast European states -- Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Montenegro, Romania and Serbia -- was held in the Serbian town of Palic on 25-29 September.
The initiative was aimed at strengthening management and leadership capacities of senior police staff and boosting collaboration in fighting organised crime.
(OSCE website, CoE website - 29/09/06)
